50|$|Organizational <b>edge</b> <b>routers</b> {{are usually}} {{configured}} to drop ingress IP traffic for these networks, which can occur either by misconfiguration, or from malicious traffic using a spoofed source address. Less commonly, ISP <b>edge</b> <b>routers</b> drop such egress traffic from customers, which reduces the impact to the Internet of such misconfigured or malicious hosts on the customer's network.|$|R
